8
00:00:33,889 --> 00:00:35,089
(Stop)

9
00:00:49,269 --> 00:00:50,409
I...

10
00:00:51,883 --> 00:00:54,853
can't forgive myself since that night.

11
00:00:56,563 --> 00:00:59,262
But with you in front of my eyes,

12
00:00:59,263 --> 00:01:01,362
I feel foolish every moment,

13
00:01:01,363 --> 00:01:03,463
expecting you to be alive.

14
00:01:09,227 --> 00:01:12,167
The past memories alone give me enough pain.

15
00:01:12,597 --> 00:01:15,697
I can't do this with you. I quit.

16
00:01:18,167 --> 00:01:20,737
- Ram Woo. - Please don't call me by that name.

17
00:01:26,677 --> 00:01:29,017
- Jung Hee Wan! - Oh, no!

18
00:01:40,797 --> 00:01:42,927
- Move it! - Make way, please!

19
00:01:45,527 --> 00:01:47,167
- Ram Woo! - Please make way!

20
00:01:47,237 --> 00:01:48,636
- Ram Woo! - Ram Woo!

21
00:01:48,637 --> 00:01:50,337
- Ram Woo! - Move!

22
00:01:51,467 --> 00:01:52,807
- Ram... - Excuse me.

23
00:01:53,207 --> 00:01:54,307
Ram Woo!

24
00:01:55,737 --> 00:01:58,107
Excuse me! Kim Ram Woo!

25
00:02:13,457 --> 00:02:15,097
(Hee Wan Tang)

26
00:02:19,427 --> 00:02:21,067
(The diet starts tomorrow.)

27
00:02:21,197 --> 00:02:23,866
To draw posters when you've come after so long?

28
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:26,036
Only when you change them seasonally...

29
00:02:26,037 --> 00:02:28,476
will the customers think this place pays attention...

30
00:02:28,477 --> 00:02:29,507
to the props.

31
00:02:29,847 --> 00:02:31,806
But why are you drawing...

32
00:02:31,807 --> 00:02:34,117
a Christmas poster when it's for the four seasons?

33
00:02:34,677 --> 00:02:36,747
No, well...

34
00:02:36,887 --> 00:02:39,957
Since I'm already at it, drawing them all is convenient.

35
00:02:40,587 --> 00:02:42,486
How's business these days? Good?

36
00:02:42,487 --> 00:02:44,557
There are ups and downs.

37
00:02:45,387 --> 00:02:46,397
Right.

38
00:02:47,957 --> 00:02:49,256
How are you in Seoul?

39
00:02:49,257 --> 00:02:50,397
I'm good.

40
00:02:50,767 --> 00:02:52,896
Why ask when you call me every day?

41
00:02:52,897 --> 00:02:55,697
As if you ever picked up my call on time.

42
00:02:55,897 --> 00:02:58,437
You pick up once every 20 calls or so.

43
00:02:59,437 --> 00:03:00,477
Hee Wan.

44
00:03:01,877 --> 00:03:03,706
Why did you drink again?

45
00:03:03,707 --> 00:03:05,776
Is it hard to sleep? Or do you have nightmares?

46
00:03:05,777 --> 00:03:07,246
No.

47
00:03:07,247 --> 00:03:09,846
I was hanging out and drinking with some school friends.

48
00:03:09,847 --> 00:03:10,887
Is that so?

49
00:03:12,217 --> 00:03:13,456
Which college friends?

50
00:03:13,457 --> 00:03:14,516
Do I know any of them?

51
00:03:14,517 --> 00:03:15,987
How would you know them?

52
00:03:16,557 --> 00:03:17,627
Really.

53
00:03:18,787 --> 00:03:20,897
- I got the green onions. - Welcome back.

54
00:03:21,897 --> 00:03:23,796
I'm sorry you must go to your part-time job...

55
00:03:23,797 --> 00:03:24,926
hungry because of me.

56
00:03:24,927 --> 00:03:26,836
Part-time job? What kind of part-time job?

57
00:03:26,837 --> 00:03:27,867
It's just a job.

58
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:29,496
Hee Ju plans to save money...

59
00:03:29,497 --> 00:03:31,137
to go free diving in Cebu with her friends.

60
00:03:33,607 --> 00:03:36,207
Come on. I told you to keep it from Hee Wan.

61
00:03:37,307 --> 00:03:39,646
We already booked our flights.

62
00:03:39,647 --> 00:03:40,877
I'm off.

63
00:03:41,377 --> 00:03:42,377
Hee Ju.

64
00:03:44,347 --> 00:03:46,287
- What? - It's dangerous.

65
00:03:47,157 --> 00:03:49,057
- Cancel it. - What am I to do?

66
00:03:49,157 --> 00:03:50,427
Do nothing?

67
00:03:50,487 --> 00:03:52,186
Should I not even meet friends...

68
00:03:52,187 --> 00:03:53,796
and live a gloomy life cooped up in my room,

69
00:03:53,797 --> 00:03:55,096
staring at the ceiling all day, just like you?

70
00:03:55,097 --> 00:03:56,097
What?

71
00:03:57,167 --> 00:03:58,466
Stop it, Hee Ju. Get going.

72
00:03:58,467 --> 00:03:59,867
I don't want to do that.

73
00:04:00,597 --> 00:04:03,806
You're right. An accident may happen on a trip.

74
00:04:03,807 --> 00:04:05,466
And I might die.

75
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:06,607
But there are other possibilities.

76
00:04:07,077 --> 00:04:09,746
I could die from a car accident as I head out...

77
00:04:09,747 --> 00:04:12,346
or from something falling onto my head on the street.

78
00:04:12,347 --> 00:04:14,677
Humans could even die while simply drinking water.

79
00:04:14,977 --> 00:04:16,276
Who knows when I'll die?

80
00:04:16,277 --> 00:04:18,747
That's why I will live my life doing things I want.

81
00:04:18,887 --> 00:04:20,186
You should too.

82
00:04:20,187 --> 00:04:22,016
Stop it. Live your life.

83
00:04:22,017 --> 00:04:23,627
Hee Wan. Just forget you heard that.

84
00:04:31,727 --> 00:04:32,727
Hee Wan?

85
00:04:40,707 --> 00:04:42,907
- Excuse me. - You scared me.

86
00:04:45,047 --> 00:04:47,446
I've been watching you from over there.

87
00:04:47,447 --> 00:04:48,976
You look terribly pale.

88
00:04:48,977 --> 00:04:50,817
It's something you often hear, yes?

89
00:04:54,217 --> 00:04:57,626
Goodness. A bad energy...

90
00:04:57,627 --> 00:04:59,586
is suppressing you.

91
00:04:59,587 --> 00:05:01,626
That's why your shoulders and lips droop,

92
00:05:01,627 --> 00:05:02,696
making you look ugly.

93
00:05:02,697 --> 00:05:05,197
Right? I know a really nice place.

94
00:05:05,227 --> 00:05:06,297
Come with me.

95
00:05:08,397 --> 00:05:09,497
Excuse me.

96
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:13,276
Because of the past incident and how much I hate you,

97
00:05:13,277 --> 00:05:15,107
I planned to ignore you.

98
00:05:15,577 --> 00:05:18,346
Gosh. But you looked too pitiful for me to walk past by.

99
00:05:18,347 --> 00:05:20,376
You look awful.

100
00:05:20,377 --> 00:05:22,776
Your energy isn't all that great.

101
00:05:22,777 --> 00:05:24,917
It's something you often hear, yes?

102
00:05:27,187 --> 00:05:30,386
I know very well what people like you need.

103
00:05:30,387 --> 00:05:32,627
I know an amazing place nearby.

104
00:05:33,957 --> 00:05:34,957
Come with me.

105
00:05:34,997 --> 00:05:36,297
To where?

106
00:05:36,497 --> 00:05:38,826
- Let's go. - Why would I?

107
00:05:38,827 --> 00:05:40,697
Come on. Trust me.

108
00:05:41,237 --> 00:05:42,436
Let's go.

109
00:05:42,437 --> 00:05:43,906
I know this place.

110
00:05:43,907 --> 00:05:46,266
It's an amazing one where you'll get...

111
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:48,237
all the good energy.

112
00:05:56,917 --> 00:05:57,946
Will it not open?

113
00:05:57,947 --> 00:06:01,217
(Eunsung High School)

114
00:06:01,417 --> 00:06:03,457
- It's open over here. - For real?

115
00:06:12,727 --> 00:06:13,967
What is it? Hurry.

116
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:53,107
What do you think?

117
00:06:53,507 --> 00:06:55,877
(Jung Hee Wan, stupid)

118
00:07:00,177 --> 00:07:02,847
Only Tae Gyeong and I know this place.

119
00:07:03,317 --> 00:07:04,487
However,

120
00:07:05,387 --> 00:07:07,516
there must be a reason...

121
00:07:07,517 --> 00:07:08,717
the school prohibits entering here.

122
00:07:09,317 --> 00:07:10,956
There might be a ghost looming here,

123
00:07:10,957 --> 00:07:13,227
or a cancer-causing agent might have been detected.

124
00:07:17,697 --> 00:07:18,727
Well,

125
00:07:20,397 --> 00:07:21,997
I'm not good at these things.

126
00:07:22,197 --> 00:07:24,267
Just do it. You don't have to be good.

127
00:07:34,277 --> 00:07:35,976
Do it, without thinking much.

128
00:07:35,977 --> 00:07:38,247
Brush it. Go.

129
00:07:39,747 --> 00:07:40,817
Go ahead.

130
00:07:50,597 --> 00:07:51,667
You know,

131
00:07:53,127 --> 00:07:55,467
a guest visits my place sometimes.

132
00:07:56,937 --> 00:07:57,967
A guest?

133
00:07:59,407 --> 00:08:01,637
Maybe a guest isn't a good way to address her.

134
00:08:03,707 --> 00:08:06,107
Anyway, I don't feel glad when I see her.

135
00:08:06,917 --> 00:08:09,217
She's the wife of someone I should call my dad.

136
00:08:09,887 --> 00:08:12,987
I'm not sure how I should address her.

137
00:08:15,587 --> 00:08:16,887
Anyway, she...

138
00:08:20,057 --> 00:08:22,957
sometimes comes to my place and leaves some money.

139
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:24,997
I guess that money is given...

140
00:08:25,427 --> 00:08:27,997
to make me not reveal who I am.

141
00:08:30,267 --> 00:08:31,907
I was always curious, though.

142
00:08:34,907 --> 00:08:37,447
Why isn't my dad coming to see me?

143
00:08:39,247 --> 00:08:40,717
Doesn't he want to know what I'm like?

144
00:08:42,277 --> 00:08:43,387
Do you want to see him?

145
00:08:50,187 --> 00:08:51,187
I'm not sure.

146
00:08:52,487 --> 00:08:54,057
I'm not sure about my feelings.

147
00:08:56,097 --> 00:08:58,797
I've been thinking about this all along since I was little,

148
00:09:02,137 --> 00:09:04,167
but I'm still not sure.

149
00:09:05,967 --> 00:09:06,977
It's the same with me.

150
00:09:10,647 --> 00:09:12,877
My mom passed away when I was four.

151
00:09:15,747 --> 00:09:17,287
On the day I entered elementary school,

152
00:09:18,047 --> 00:09:21,157
among many people all smiling, only my dad was crying.

153
00:09:21,387 --> 00:09:23,117
I asked him why he was crying,

154
00:09:23,827 --> 00:09:26,657
and he said, "Your mom really wanted to be here."

155
00:09:27,227 --> 00:09:30,027
He said he cried because he missed my mom so much.

156
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:34,897
I...

157
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:37,006
was too little...

158
00:09:37,007 --> 00:09:39,207
to have memories about my mom,

159
00:09:39,437 --> 00:09:41,776
but I cried after my dad...

160
00:09:41,777 --> 00:09:43,377
and said I missed my mom.

161
00:09:44,177 --> 00:09:46,006
But honestly, I'm not sure.

162
00:09:46,007 --> 00:09:47,716
I'm not sure whether I really miss her...

163
00:09:47,717 --> 00:09:49,917
or I have to miss her.

164
00:10:17,847 --> 00:10:18,847
Sit here.

165
00:10:19,877 --> 00:10:20,977
- I mean, - Like this.

166
00:10:21,477 --> 00:10:23,516
you're splattering the paint. Stop it.

167
00:10:23,517 --> 00:10:24,747
- Here I go. - Watch out!

168
00:10:26,487 --> 00:10:27,917
Are you out of your mind?

169
00:10:28,087 --> 00:10:29,717
- Shall I make dots? - Yes.

170
00:10:30,327 --> 00:10:32,426
Can you move over a bit?

171
00:10:32,427 --> 00:10:33,997
Please go.

172
00:10:36,127 --> 00:10:37,827
All right.

173
00:10:41,837 --> 00:10:42,867
Do what I do.

174
00:10:45,837 --> 00:10:48,337
This looks like a night sky.

175
00:10:50,477 --> 00:10:51,477
I know.

176
00:11:03,527 --> 00:11:04,527
Look.

177
00:11:05,157 --> 00:11:06,187
This is a shooting star.

178
00:11:07,197 --> 00:11:09,657
This makes it a shooting star.

179
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:16,737
This makes it...

180
00:11:17,567 --> 00:11:18,607
Saturn.

181
00:11:30,887 --> 00:11:31,917
What's going on?

182
00:11:34,557 --> 00:11:35,557
Hi.

183
00:11:35,987 --> 00:11:37,387
Why is Hee Wan here?

184
00:11:37,957 --> 00:11:39,956
He was feeling lost,

185
00:11:39,957 --> 00:11:41,697
so I helped him refresh himself.

186
00:11:42,997 --> 00:11:44,597
We promised that only two of us come here.

187
00:11:46,027 --> 00:11:47,297
And you brought him without telling me.

188
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:50,906
- I forgot. - And,

189
00:11:50,907 --> 00:11:52,307
why didn't you answer my instant message?

190
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:55,137
- We need to make a reservation... - The weekend.

191
00:11:55,977 --> 00:11:57,047
I forgot.

192
00:11:57,807 --> 00:12:00,176
I'm going to Seoul with my dad for house hunting on the weekend.

193
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:01,177
I'm sorry.

194
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:04,447
My dad suddenly told me that he's only available then.

195
00:12:07,217 --> 00:12:09,387
Is a promise with me nothing to you?

196
00:12:09,887 --> 00:12:11,527
What are you saying?

197
00:12:11,727 --> 00:12:12,757
I'm sorry.

198
00:12:13,157 --> 00:12:16,497
These days, I'm busy with the college stuff.

199
00:12:17,497 --> 00:12:18,497
All right.

200
00:12:20,237 --> 00:12:22,997
You're busy, so you don't have to tell me everything from now on.

201
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:27,007
You're only interested in hanging out with your new friend.

202
00:12:28,837 --> 00:12:30,076
Listening to your stories about passing the college...

203
00:12:30,077 --> 00:12:31,807
actually made me sick.

204
00:12:32,047 --> 00:12:33,677
- Tae Gyeong, it's not like that... - It made you sick?

205
00:12:34,977 --> 00:12:36,217
That's pretty harsh.

206
00:12:40,957 --> 00:12:42,257
You look like you have chemistry.

207
00:12:43,417 --> 00:12:44,557
Take care and have fun.

208
00:12:45,027 --> 00:12:46,027
Wait.

209
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:47,756
Why are you doing this?

210
00:12:47,757 --> 00:12:48,957
What's wrong with you?

211
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:51,797
Goodness.

212
00:13:03,177 --> 00:13:04,707
- This is unbelievable. - What is it?

213
00:13:06,877 --> 00:13:08,247
I didn't know it was still here.

214
00:13:12,287 --> 00:13:13,517
How is Tae Gyeong doing?

215
00:13:14,217 --> 00:13:15,217
Tae Gyeong?

216
00:13:17,787 --> 00:13:18,857
Well,

217
00:13:19,657 --> 00:13:20,927
I don't know.

218
00:13:22,457 --> 00:13:24,227
What are you saying? Did you have an argument again?

219
00:13:27,067 --> 00:13:28,667
I guess she isn't in Korea now.

220
00:13:30,837 --> 00:13:32,037
Then what about Hong Seok?

221
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,437
We don't keep in touch.

222
00:13:36,407 --> 00:13:38,606
The only friend left for you from the high school years...

223
00:13:38,607 --> 00:13:40,647
is a grim reaper, me? That's a big problem.

224
00:13:43,687 --> 00:13:44,787
How can I open this?

225
00:13:48,487 --> 00:13:49,517
You know what I think?

226
00:13:50,557 --> 00:13:51,957
I should go see Hong Seok.

227
00:13:52,187 --> 00:13:53,187
Darn it.

228
00:13:58,997 --> 00:14:00,197
I miss him.

229
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:02,067
I want to see Hong Seok.

230
00:14:02,197 --> 00:14:04,567
- So I should go see him first. - Come on.

231
00:14:07,307 --> 00:14:08,337
What are you doing?

232
00:14:11,547 --> 00:14:12,577
All right.

233
00:14:13,177 --> 00:14:15,617
Let me see. Let's take a look.

234
00:14:15,647 --> 00:14:18,247
Where's Hong Seok's number?

235
00:14:21,157 --> 00:14:22,157
(Lee Hong Seok)

236
00:14:22,158 --> 00:14:23,187
There it is.

237
00:14:24,087 --> 00:14:25,627
When I see Hong Seok...

238
00:14:25,927 --> 00:14:27,097
(Lee Hong Seok)

239
00:14:28,897 --> 00:14:29,927
That little...

240
00:14:30,157 --> 00:14:32,497
We should play board games with him. That will be the first thing we do.

241
00:14:37,807 --> 00:14:38,837
- Gosh. - Come on.

242
00:14:39,107 --> 00:14:40,807
You must have lost your mind. Seriously.

243
00:14:44,377 --> 00:14:45,907
I'm sure he deleted my number.

244
00:14:51,147 --> 00:14:52,347
Wait. No, he didn't.

245
00:14:52,847 --> 00:14:53,857
Hey, you...

246
00:14:55,187 --> 00:14:56,587
- Hello. - Hey.

247
00:14:59,157 --> 00:15:00,627
- Is this... - What's this about?

248
00:15:03,997 --> 00:15:06,267
I'm working right now. I'm hanging up.

249
00:15:13,337 --> 00:15:14,337
Happy now?

250
00:15:14,877 --> 00:15:18,407
All right. Meet my friend, Hong Seok.

251
00:15:18,547 --> 00:15:19,946
Hey, you can't do that.

252
00:15:19,947 --> 00:15:21,747
This should be the least of your worries right now.

253
00:15:22,917 --> 00:15:23,987
The real question is...

254
00:15:25,547 --> 00:15:26,947
how you're going to get out of here.

255
00:15:28,787 --> 00:15:29,987
Come on.

256
00:15:32,557 --> 00:15:34,927
If you agree to meet with Hong Seok, I'll open it for you.

257
00:15:37,927 --> 00:15:39,427
Do you plan on staying in there?

258
00:15:39,827 --> 00:15:41,237
I got it. Just open it.

259
00:15:43,097 --> 00:15:45,067
(Restricted Area, Authorized Personnel Only)

260
00:15:50,007 --> 00:15:51,047
(Meet my friend, Hong Seok.)

261
00:15:54,317 --> 00:15:56,517
(Meet my friend, Hong Seok.)

262
00:15:56,717 --> 00:15:57,717
Thank you.

263
00:16:00,757 --> 00:16:03,287
(Eunsung High School)

264
00:16:04,157 --> 00:16:06,456
Listen up, my friend. Here's an important piece of advice.

265
00:16:06,457 --> 00:16:09,256
You cannot take anyone's side in this fight.

266
00:16:09,257 --> 00:16:12,627
Taking sides would be crossing the point of no return.

267
00:16:12,797 --> 00:16:13,896
What should I do?

268
00:16:13,897 --> 00:16:15,997
I'm partially responsible for this.

269
00:16:16,037 --> 00:16:17,367
Here's what I think.

270
00:16:18,437 --> 00:16:19,837
Since this happened on school grounds,

271
00:16:20,137 --> 00:16:21,736
we must get out of here.

272
00:16:21,737 --> 00:16:22,737
I see.

273
00:16:24,247 --> 00:16:26,177
It sounds like you just want to go on a trip.

274
00:16:27,007 --> 00:16:28,016
